  "texts": [
    "Let ⟨C(γ)⟩ be the p = 1 QAOA objective for weighted MaxCut on trianglefree (D + 1)-regular graphs as given in Equation (9), with β = π 8.",
    "The partial derivatives of ⟨C(γ)⟩ with respect to the weights w ij satisfy,∂⟨C(γ)⟩ ∂w ij ≤ 1 2 + (1 + γ)|w ij | 2 + γ 4 v∈nbhd(i)/{j} |w iv | + u∈nbhd(j)/{i} |w uj |(29)Proof.",
    "We define for convenience,T uv = w uv sin(w uv γ) k∈nbhd(u)/{v} cos(w uk γ) + t∈nbhd(v)/{u} cos(w vt γ) so that ⟨C(γ)⟩ = {u,v}∈E wuv 2 + Tuv 4.",
    "Clearly, ∂⟨C(γ)⟩ ∂w ij = 1 2 + 1 4 {u,v}∈E ∂Tuv ∂w ij.To determine the last term, we have four cases, 1. u = i; v = j: In T uv, the term inside the parenthesis is upper bounded by 2 and independent of w ij.",
